Just before midnight somewhere in the western United States, a white pickup truck’s high beams light up a stretch of dark highway.
They’re engulfed in a smell that intensifies as they walk: a blend of barnyard animal, excrement, and decaying flesh.
The animals in these so-called gestation crates appear not to be able to turn around or even take a step.
Reaching into a pen, the group’s leader helps to free one squealing piglet whose foot is caught in the grate.
They return to one pen where, the night before, they freed a group of injured piglets caught under a cage door.